<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ff260f7c-e201-4865-ba72-91fa17b19823" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>10.2.25</sptc><title id="_7468a022-2aae-453c-b153-d9abdae9123a">Shower area floor membrane application</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_acbe5c6a-b9ce-4153-8ecd-b0949921efaa" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_69090a2c-e745-4bb3-9de8-204243d79fb7">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>For hobless showers, or showers with hobs or stepdowns, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_2945049e-e938-4cc6-81c4-677ca172a461" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref> must be applied over the floor and up the vertical face of the wall substrate to a minimum height of 1800 mm above the finished tile level of the floor.</p></subclause></clause>